*R1.* What is the difference between a host and an end system? List several different types of end systems. Is a Web server an end system? 

_There is no difference. Smartphones, PCs, Macs, smart fridges, Teslas (the cars), etc. A Web server is an application that is ran on an end system._

*R2.* Describe the protocol that might be used by two people having a telephonic  conversation to initiate and end the conversation, i.e., the way that they talk. 

_1. One of the two people dials the other's phone number._

_2. The person on the receiving side either answers or declines the phone call._

_3. If the phone call was accepted, the two parties then proceed to having a conversation using on of the spoken languages._

_4. After the conversation is over, both people hang up, ending the phone call._

*R3.* Why are standards important for protocols?

_The standards are important because the way both parties communicate must be uniform and precise. If one of the parties doesn't follow the standard, the other cannot comprehend the messages from that party. Two people speaking different spoken languages don't understand each other because there is no common standard between them._




